# 1. Types of Nodes

## Definition

An Ethereum Node is a computer or system that participates in the Ethereum blockchain network.

Ethereum is a:

- Peer-to-Peer (P2P)
- Public
- Permissionless

blockchain network.

---

## A) Full Node

### Definition

A Full Node stores the complete blockchain and validates transactions and blocks.

### Features

- Stores complete blockchain data
- Validates blocks and transactions
- Provides blockchain data to other nodes
- High storage requirement

---

## B) Light Node

### Definition

A Light Node stores only block headers and retrieves additional data when required.

### Features

- Stores block headers only
- Uses Root Hashes for verification
- Fetches data on demand
- Suitable for mobile and low-storage devices

---

## C) Archive Node

### Definition

An Archive Node stores everything contained in a Full Node along with all previous blockchain states.

### Features

- Stores complete blockchain
- Stores historical blockchain states
- Used by block explorers and wallets
- Very high storage requirement

---

# Comparison of Nodes

| Full Node | Light Node | Archive Node |
|------------|------------|--------------|
| Full blockchain | Block headers only | Full blockchain + previous states |
| Validates blocks | Fetches data | Stores historical data |
| High storage | Low storage | Very high storage |

